**Root cause:** VAA breadth multiplied allocation by fractional breadth (e.g., 3/5 positive = 60% of target weight), then vol_scale capped at 1.0, so positions were being shrunk twice. With breadth ranging 0.2–1.0, expected investment = ~60–95% of target. Combined with vol cap, mean drawdown only 11% confirms capital is sitting idle.

**V9 switch:** Cross-Asset Momentum with Trend Filter — fully invested (95%) in top-2 momentum assets above 200-day SMA, falling back to best safe haven when fewer qualify. Vol scaling only reduces (not caps up).

